  "root_text": {
    "snp5.6:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 5.6 ",
    "snp5.6:0.2": "Dhotakamāṇavapucchā ",
    "snp5.6:1.1": "“Pucchāmi taṁ bhagavā brūhi metaṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:1.2": "(iccāyasmā dhotako) ",
    "snp5.6:1.3": "Vācābhikaṅkhāmi mahesi tuyhaṁ; ",
    "snp5.6:1.4": "Tava sutvāna nigghosaṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:1.5": "Sikkhe nibbānamattano”. ",
    "snp5.6:2.1": "“Tenahātappaṁ karohi, ",
    "snp5.6:2.2": "(dhotakāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp5.6:2.3": "Idheva nipako sato; ",
    "snp5.6:2.4": "Ito sutvāna nigghosaṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:2.5": "Sikkhe nibbānamattano”. ",
    "snp5.6:3.1": "“Passāmahaṁ devamanussaloke, ",
    "snp5.6:3.2": "Akiñcanaṁ brāhmaṇamiriyamānaṁ; ",
    "snp5.6:3.3": "Taṁ taṁ namassāmi samantacakkhu, ",
    "snp5.6:3.4": "Pamuñca maṁ sakka kathaṅkathāhi”. ",
    "snp5.6:4.1": "“Nāhaṁ sahissāmi pamocanāya, ",
    "snp5.6:4.2": "Kathaṅkathiṁ dhotaka kañci loke; ",
    "snp5.6:4.3": "Dhammañca seṭṭhaṁ abhijānamāno, ",
    "snp5.6:4.4": "Evaṁ tuvaṁ oghamimaṁ taresi”. ",
    "snp5.6:5.1": "“Anusāsa brahme karuṇāyamāno, ",
    "snp5.6:5.2": "Vivekadhammaṁ yamahaṁ vijaññaṁ; ",
    "snp5.6:5.3": "Yathāhaṁ ākāsova abyāpajjamāno, ",
    "snp5.6:5.4": "Idheva santo asito careyyaṁ”. ",
    "snp5.6:6.1": "“Kittayissāmi te santiṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:6.2": "(dhotakāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp5.6:6.3": "Diṭṭhe dhamme anītihaṁ; ",
    "snp5.6:6.4": "Yaṁ viditvā sato caraṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:6.5": "Tare loke visattikaṁ”. ",
    "snp5.6:7.1": "“Tañcāhaṁ abhinandāmi, ",
    "snp5.6:7.2": "mahesi santimuttamaṁ; ",
    "snp5.6:7.3": "Yaṁ viditvā sato caraṁ, ",
    "snp5.6:7.4": "tare loke visattikaṁ”. ",
    "snp5.6:8.1": "“Yaṁ kiñci sampajānāsi, ",
    "snp5.6:8.2": "(dhotakāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp5.6:8.3": "Uddhaṁ adho tiriyañcāpi majjhe; ",
    "snp5.6:8.4": "Etaṁ viditvā saṅgoti loke, ",
    "snp5.6:8.5": "Bhavābhavāya mākāsi taṇhan”ti. ",
    "snp5.6:8.6": "Dhotakamāṇavapucchā pañcamī. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp5.6:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 5.6 ",
    "snp5.6:0.2": "The Questions of Dhotaka ",
    "snp5.6:1.1": "“I ask you, Blessed One; please tell me this,” ",
    "snp5.6:1.2": "said Venerable Dhotaka, ",
    "snp5.6:1.3": "“I long for your voice, great seer. ",
    "snp5.6:1.4": "After hearing your message, ",
    "snp5.6:1.5": "I shall train myself for extinguishment.” ",
    "snp5.6:2.1": "“Well then, be keen, alert,” ",
    "snp5.6:2.2": "replied the Buddha, ",
    "snp5.6:2.3": "“and mindful right here. ",
    "snp5.6:2.4": "After hearing this message, go on ",
    "snp5.6:2.5": "and train yourself for extinguishment.” ",
    "snp5.6:3.1": "“I see in the world of gods and humans ",
    "snp5.6:3.2": "a brahmin travelling with nothing. ",
    "snp5.6:3.3": "I bow especially to you, All-seer: ",
    "snp5.6:3.4": "release me, Sakyan, from my indecisions.” ",
    "snp5.6:4.1": "“I am not able to release anyone ",
    "snp5.6:4.2": "in the world who is indecisive, Dhotaka. ",
    "snp5.6:4.3": "But when you understand the best of teachings, ",
    "snp5.6:4.4": "you shall cross this flood.” ",
    "snp5.6:5.1": "“Teach me, brahmin, out of compassion, ",
    "snp5.6:5.2": "the principle of seclusion so that I may understand. ",
    "snp5.6:5.3": "I wish to practice right here, peaceful, independent, ",
    "snp5.6:5.4": "unobstructed as space itself.” ",
    "snp5.6:6.1": "“I shall extol that peace for you,” ",
    "snp5.6:6.2": "replied the Buddha, ",
    "snp5.6:6.3": "“that is apparent in the present, <j>not relying on tradition. ",
    "snp5.6:6.4": "Having understood it, one who lives mindfully ",
    "snp5.6:6.5": "may cross over clinging in the world.” ",
    "snp5.6:7.1": "“And I rejoice, great seer, ",
    "snp5.6:7.2": "in that supreme peace, ",
    "snp5.6:7.3": "having understood which, one who lives mindfully ",
    "snp5.6:7.4": "may cross over clinging in the world.” ",
    "snp5.6:8.1": "“Once you have understood that everything,” ",
    "snp5.6:8.2": "replied the Buddha, ",
    "snp5.6:8.3": "“you are aware of in the world—",
    "snp5.6:8.4": "above, below, all round, between—",
    "snp5.6:8.5": "is a snare, don’t crave for life after life.” "
  },
